Peru:
Fujimori was re-hospitalized for medical tests
Former President Alberto Fujimori was on Tuesday admitted to a public hospital to investigate the loss of his muscular legs, informed his family doctor.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, who is serving 25 years in prison for violating human rights during his reign (1990-2000), has several illnesses, including cancer of the tongue, which operates four times and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Congressman and his personal physician, told the television that Fujimori hospital for three days in the Peruvian Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas were examined to determine the cause of his pain and muscle loss in the lower limbs.
Aguinaga, commented that in his opinion, Fujimori could be pardoned on humanitarian grounds. Nevertheless, he wished it not because he think he&#39;s innocent.
He was operated on four times in tongue cancer and he has lost 18 kg weight. There are other diseases such as severe erosive gastritis, a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and circulatory problems in the legs were at the doctor.
Fujimori is since September 2007 in the prison Dirección Nacional de Operaciones Especiales de la policía.
In April 2009 he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the murder of 25 people by the death squads of the Peruvian army, that was during his reign secretly operates.
